  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Educators can use ChatGPT to create virtual teaching assistants or intelligent tutors to help students solve problems, answer questions, or offer personalized learning advice.",
    "ChatGPT can also be used to simulate conversational learning environments, helping students improve their language communication skills (Baidoo-Anu & Ansah, 2023; Kasneci et al., 2023).",
    "However, ChatGPT's use also poses ethical and educational challenges.",
    "Since its generated content might be automated, there are concerns about the accuracy and reliability of the information.",
    "In educational settings, ChatGPT-generated dialogues might mislead students with inaccurate information, affecting their learning outcomes."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "ChatGPT can also be used to simulate conversational learning environments, helping students improve their language communication skills (Baidoo-Anu & Ansah, 2023; Kasneci et al., 2023)."
